n%20Gaza%20and%20the%20lives%20of%20more%20than%20two%20million%20Palestinians%20hanging%20in%20the%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Israeli%20statement%2C%20the%20extension%20would%20see%20half%20of%20the%20hostages%20still%20in%20Gaza%20released%20on%20the%20day%20the%20deal%20comes%20into%20effect%2C%20with%20the%20rest%20to%20be%20released%20at%20the%20end%20if%20agreement%20is%20reached%20on%20a%20permanent%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20immediate%20response%20from%20Hamas%2C%20which%20earlier%20rejected%20the%20idea%20of%20an%20extension.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20backing%20of%20what%20it%20described%20as%20a%20US%20plan%20comes%20amid%20a%20flurry%20of%20warnings%20not%20to%20restart%20the%20war%2C%20which%20after%2015%20months%20devastated%20Gaza%2C%20displaced%20almost%20the%20entire%20population%20of%20the%20coastal%20strip%20and%20sparked%20a%20hunger%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnited%20Nations%20head%20Antonio%20Guterres%20warned%20against%20a%20%26quot%3Bcatastrophic%26quot%3B%20return%20to%20war%20and%20said%20that%20a%20%26quot%3Bpermanent%20ceasefire%20and%20the%20release%20of%20all%20hostages%20are%20essential%20to%20preventing%20escalation%20and%20averting%20more%20devastating%20consequences%20for%20civilians%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20officials%20engaged%20in%20ceasefire%20negotiations%20with%20Egyptian%2C%20Qatari%20and%20American%20mediators%20in%20Cairo%20last%20week.%20But%20by%20early%20Saturday%20there%20was%20no%20sign%20of%20consensus%20as%20Muslims%20in%20Gaza%20marked%20the%20first%20day%20of%20Ramadan%20with%20coloured%20lights%20brightening%20war-damaged%20neighbourhoods.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20Hamas%20official%20told%20AFP%20the%20Palestinian%20militant%20group%20was%20prepared%20to%20release%20all%20remaining%20hostages%20in%20a%20single%20swap%20during%20the%20second%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHamas%20will%20not%20be%20happy%20to%20drag%20on%20phase%20one%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20really%20have%20the%20capacity%20to%20force%20Israel%20to%20go%20on%20to%20phase%20two%2C%26quot%3B%20Max%20Rodenbeck%2C%20an%20analyst%20for%20the%20International%20Crisis%20Group%2C%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHamas%20hostage%20video%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20six-week%20ceasefire%20that%20took%20effect%20on%20January%2019%2C%20Gaza%20militants%20freed%2025%20living%20hostages%20and%20returned%20the%20bodies%20of%20eight%20others%20to%20Israel%2C%20in%20exchange%20for%20hundreds%20of%20Palestinian%20prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%2C%20reached%20following%20months%20of%20gruelling%20negotiations%2C%20largely%20halted%20the%20war%20that%20erupted%20with%20Hamas's%20October%207%2C%202023%20attack%20on%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Hamas%20on%20several%20occasions%20reiterated%20its%20%26quot%3Breadiness%20to%20engage%20in%20negotiations%20for%20its%20second%20phase%26quot%3B%2C%20Israel%20preferred%20to%20secure%20more%20hostage%20releases%20under%20an%20extension%20of%20the%20first%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Palestinian%20source%20close%20to%20the%20talks%20told%20AFP%20that%20Israel%20had%20proposed%20to%20extend%20the%20first%20phase%20in%20successive%20one-week%20intervals%20with%20a%20view%20to%20conducting%20hostage-prisoner%20swaps%20each%20week%2C%20adding%20that%20Hamas%20had%20rejected%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20251%20hostages%20taken%20during%20Hamas's%20October%207%20attack%2C%2058%20hostages%20remain%20in%20Gaza%2C%20including%2034%20the%20Israeli%20military%20says%20are%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHamas's%20armed%20wing%20released%20footage%20showing%20what%20appeared%20to%20be%20a%20group%20of%20Israeli%20hostages%20in%20Gaza%2C%20accompanied%20with%20the%20message%3A%20%26quot%3BOnly%20a%20ceasefire%20agreement%20brings%20them%20back%20alive%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAFP%20was%20unable%20to%20immediately%20verify%20the%20video%2C%20the%20latest%20that%20militants%20have%20released%20of%20Gaza%20captives.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetanyahu's%20office%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bcruel%20propaganda%26quot%3B%20but%20Israeli%20campaign%20group%20the%20Hostages%20and%20Missing%20Families%20Forum%20said%20the%20Horn%20family%2C%20two%20of%20whose%20members%20appear%20in%20the%20video%2C%20had%20given%20permission%20for%20the%20footage%20of%20them%20to%20be%20published.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli-Argentinian%20Yair%20Horn%20was%20released%20on%20February%2015%20but%20his%20brother%20Eitan%20remains%20in%20captivity%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20demand%20from%20the%20decision-makers%3A%20Look%20Eitan%20in%20the%20eyes.%20Don't%20stop%20the%20agreement%20that%20has%20already%20brought%20dozens%20of%20hostages%20back%20to%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20family%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ENetanyahu's%20coalition%20worries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDomestic%20political%20considerations%20are%20a%20factor%20in%20Netanyahu's%20reluctance%20to%20begin%20the%20planned%20second%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinance%20Minister%20Bezalel%20Smotrich%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20far-right%20faction%20in%20the%20governing%20coalition%2C%20has%20threatened%20to%20quit%20if%20the%20war%20is%20not%20resumed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Israeli%20government%20could%20fall%20if%20we%20enter%20phase%20two%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michael%20Horowitz%2C%20head%20of%20intelligence%20for%20risk%20management%20consultancy%20Le%20Beck%20International.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20has%20said%20it%20needs%20to%20retain%20troops%20in%20a%20strip%20of%20Gaza%20along%20the%20Egyptian%20border%20to%20stop%20arms%20smuggling%20by%20Hamas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20truce%20has%20enabled%20greater%20aid%20flows%20into%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20where%20around%2070%20percent%20of%20buildings%20were%20damaged%20or%20destroyed%2C%20almost%20the%20entire%20population%20was%20disp