dership%20and%20innovative%20products%20are%20part%20of%20Nvidia's%20success.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia%20has%20been%20around%20for%20over%20three%20decades%2C%20but%20the%20chipmaker%20became%20a%20household%20name%20only%20in%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia%20was%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efounded%20in%201993%20by%20Jensen%20Huang%2C%20Chris%20Malachowsky%2C%20and%20Curtis%20Priem%20%26quot%3Bwith%20a%20vision%20to%20bring%203D%20graphics%20to%20the%20gaming%20and%20multimedia%20markets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20boom%20in%20AI%20technology%20has%20made%20it%20one%20of%20the%20most%20valuable%20companies%20in%20the%20world%20as%20companies%20scramble%20to%20buy%20its%20graphics%20processing%20units.%20Here's%20what%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20Nvidia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fee17178-88ce-4f0e-894f-f688efd2a634%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistory%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nvidia-ai-chip-graphics-card-company-was-started-dennys-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENvidia's%20origin%20story%20began%20at%20a%20Denny's%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20meeting%20between%20Huang%20%E2%80%94%20who%20once%20worked%20for%20the%20chain%20%E2%80%94%20Malachowsky%20and%20Priem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPersonal%20computing%20was%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20taking%20off%2C%20and%20the%20trio%20sought%20a%20way%20to%20capitalize%20on%20it.%20Huang%20said%20in%20a%202010%20interview%20with%20Stanford%20University's%20engineering%20school%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bwondered%20whether%20starting%20a%20graphics%20company%20would%20be%20a%20good%20idea.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20brainstormed%20and%20fantasized%20about%20what%20kind%20of%20company%20it%20would%20be%20and%20the%20world%20we%20could%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20fun.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20goal%20was%20to%20improve%20the%20experience%20of%20gaming%20on%20a%20PC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201999%2C%20the%20year%20it%20went%20public%2C%20Nvidia%20had%20invented%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-gpus-cpus-parallel-computing-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egraphics%20processing%20unit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20computer%20chip%20that%20can%20handle%20many%20tasks%20simultaneously.%20It%20had%20faced%20challenges%3B%20it%20built%20two%20chips%20that%20failed%2C%20and%20it%20nearly%20went%20bankrupt.%20But%20it%20had%20also%20established%20itself%20as%20a%20formidable%20player%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20partnering%20with%20companies%20such%20as%20Sega%2C%20Dell%2C%20and%20Micron%20and%20winning%20rounds%20of%20funding%20from%20the%20venture%20firms%20Sequoia%20Capital%20and%20Sierra%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202006%2C%20it%20released%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-cuda-software-gpu-ai-chips-cerebras-ipo-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECUDA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20general-purpose%20programming%20interface%20that%20would%20expand%20its%20business%20far%20beyond%20gaming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Sequoia%20Capital's%20%26quot%3BCrucible%20Moments%26quot%3B%20podcast%2C%20Andrew%20Ng%2C%20a%20Stanford%20professor%20who%20founded%20Google%20Brain%2C%20recalled%20his%20students%20telling%20him%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20Andrew%2C%20there's%20this%20thing%20called%20CUDA%20%E2%80%94%20not%20that%20easy%20to%20program%2C%20but%20it's%20letting%20people%20use%20GPUs%20for%20something%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20started%20to%20see%2010x%20or%20even%20100x%20speedups%20training%20neural%20networks%20on%20GPUs%20because%20we%20could%20do%201%2C000%20or%2010%2C000%20things%20in%20parallel%20rather%20than%20one%20step%20after%20another%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia's%20GPUs%20were%20used%20to%20train%20AlexNet%2C%20an%20image%20classification%20system%20unveiled%20in%202012%20that%20significantly%20influenced%20the%20field%20of%20deep%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20launch%20of%20ChatGPT%20in%20late%202022%20ushered%20Nvidia%20into%20a%20new%20era.%20The%20chipmaker's%20shares%20surged%20by%20more%20than%20800%25%20from%20the%20start%20of%202023%20to%20the%20start%20of%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20that%20growth%20came%20from%20the%20success%20of%20Nvidia's%20H100%20chip%2C%20which%20it%20released%20in%20March%202022.%20The%20%2440%2C000%20chip%2C%20named%20for%20the%20computer%20scientist%20Grace%20Hopper%2C%20has%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20providing%20the%20computing%20power%20for%20large%20language%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b8cd7e36-ec5d-46be-9d28-5aa7b9c3b0c4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeadership%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia's%20success%20may%20be%20best%20personified%20by%20its%20CEO%3A%20Jensen%20Huang.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%2061-year-old%20bona%20fide%20tech%20mogul%2C%20Huang%20has%20a%20net%20worth%20of%20about%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%24110%20billion.%20While%20some%20execs%20sport%20chains%20or%20Patagonia%20vests%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjensen-huang-wardrobe-black-leather-jackets-signature-look-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHuang%20is%20often%20spotted%20in%20a%20leather%20jacket%3C%2Fa%3E.%20BI%20identified%20at%20least%20six%20versions%20he's%20worn%20over%20the%20years%2C%20including%20a%20nearly%20%249%2C000%20lizard-embossed%20coat%20from%20Tom%20Ford%20he%20wore%20at%20the%20company's%20global%20AI%20conference%2C%20GTC%2C%20in%202024.%20He%20commemorated%20Nvidia's%20stock%20price%20hitting%20%24100%20with%20a%20tattoo%20of%20Nvidia's%20logo%20on%20his%20arm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22911%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jensen%20Huang%20smiling%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bf8dfab1834fe311659697%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJensen%20Huang%20in%20one%20of%20his%20many%20leather%20jackets.%3Cp%3EMOHD%20RASFAN%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHuang's%20early%20years%20were%20tumultuous.%20He%20was%20born%20in%20Taiwan%2C%20and%20he%20spent%20time%20there%20and%20in%20Thailand%20before%20his%20parents%20sent%20him%20to%20the%20United%20States%20because%20of%20social%20unrest%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20attended%20a%20reform%20school%20in%20Kentucky.%20In%20an%20interview%20with%20NPR%20in%202012%2C%20he%20recalled%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20kids%20were%20really%20tough%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BThey%20all%20had%20pocket%20knives%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20they%20get%20in%20fights%2C%20it's%20not%20pretty.%20Kids%20get%20hurt.%26quot%3B%20He%20later%20moved%20to%20Oregon%2C%20where%20he%20was%20reunited%20with%20his%20parents.%20In%20high%20school%2C%20he%20became%20a%20nationally%20ranked%20table%20tennis%20champion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuang%20graduated%20from%20Oregon%20State%20University%20with%20a%20degree%20in%20electrical%20engineering%20in%201984.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20freshman%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-ceo-jensen-huang-how-he-met-his-wife-lori-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHuang%20met%20Lori%20Mills%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20his%20future%20wife.%20In%20an%20interview%20at%20the%20Hong%20Kong%20University%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology%2C%20he%20said%20he%20won%20her%20over%20by%20offering%20to%20help%20her%20with%20her%20homework.%20They%20married%20five%20years%20after%20meeting%20and%20now%20have%20two%20children%3A%20Madison%20Huang%2C%20a%20marketing%20director%20at%20Nvidia%2C%20and%20Spencer%20Huang%2C%20a%20senior%20product%20manager%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJensen%20Huang%20later%20earned%20a%20master's%20in%20electrical%20engineering%20from%20Stanford%20and%20he%20worked%20at%20the%20chip%20companies%20LSI%20Logic%20and%20Advanced%20Micro%20Devices%20before%20launching%20Nvidia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuang%20sold%20about%201.3%20million%20shares%20of%20Nvidia%20when%20the%20company%20hit%20a%20%243%20trillion%20market%20cap%20in%20June%202024%2C%20but%20he%20retains%20a%20more%20than%203%25%20stake%20in%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22af8705e7-d29b-4da5-b707-66ebfb6975cf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EProducts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Image%20of%20Nvidia%20Blackwell%20semiconductor%20chip%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cefb0bc72ebc54a40f8832%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENvidia's%20next-generation%20Blackwell%20chips%20have%20attracted%20customers%2C%20including%20SoftBank%2C%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%2C%20and%20Microsoft.%3Cp%3ENvidia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia's%20business%20is%20built%20around%20GPUs%2C%20which%20can%20handle%20tasks%20simultaneously%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20central%20processing%20units%2C%20or%20CPUs%2C%20which%20are%20in%20standard%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia's%20GPUs%20have%20become%20a%20mainstay%20of%20the%20AI%20revolution%20because%20they%20provide%20the%20computing%20power%20needed%20to%20run%20massive%20large%20language%20models%20like%20OpenAI's%20GPT-4%20and%20Meta's%20Llama%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemand%20for%20Nvidia's%20H100%20chips%2C%20built%20on%20its%20Hopper%20architecture%2C%20has%20been%20so%20high%20in%20late%202023%20and%202024%20that%20tech%20execs%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20bragged%20about%20how%20many%20units%20they're%20training%20new%20technology%20on.%20ByteDance%20has%20found%20workarounds%20to%20US%20export%20bans%20on%20the%20chips%20to%20China.%3Cstrong%3E%20%