employee-one-on-one-meeting-strategy-for-promotions-2025-2%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20AI-focused%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20work%20about%2060%20hours%20weekly%20for%20increased%20productivity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWorkplace%20experts%20argue%20longer%20hours%20can%20reduce%20productivity%20due%20to%20errors%20and%20decreased%20motivation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20founder%20instead%20looks%20for%20%26quot%3Bburstable%20bandwidth%26quot%3B%20where%20workers%20can%20ramp%20up%20when%20needed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Googlers%20working%20on%20AI%2C%2060%20could%20be%20the%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-day-workweek-us-half-day-fridays-pros-and-cons-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E40%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsergey-brin-career-life-education%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESergey%20Brin%3C%2Fa%3E%20sees%20working%20about%2060%20hours%20a%20week%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20sweet%20spot%20of%20productivity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20recommending%20that%20workers%20focusing%20on%20Gemini%2C%20the%20company's%20AI%20model%2C%20go%20well%20beyond%20the%2040%20hours%20typical%20of%20many%20workplaces%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20cofounder%20advised%20in%20a%20recent%20memo%20that%20they%20consider%20being%20in%20the%20office%20%26quot%3Bat%20least%26quot%3B%20every%20weekday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F02%2F27%2Ftechnology%2Fgoogle-sergey-brin-return-to-office.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20New%20York%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20my%20experience%2C%20about%2060%20hours%20a%20week%20is%20the%20sweet%20spot%20of%20productivity%2C%26quot%3B%20Brin%20wrote%20in%20the%20memo%20published%20in%20full%20by%20The%20Verge.%20%26quot%3BSome%20folks%20put%20in%20a%20lot%20more%20but%20can%20burn%20out%20or%20lose%20creativity.%20A%20number%20of%20folks%20work%20less%20than%2060%20hours%20and%20a%20small%20number%20put%20in%20the%20bare%20minimum%20to%20get%20by.%20This%20last%20group%20is%20not%20only%20unproductive%20but%20also%20can%20be%20highly%20demoralizing%20to%20everyone%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20for%20many%20employees%2C%20more%20time%20at%20their%20desks%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20they'll%20be%20more%20productive%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20extra%20hours%20could%20even%20hurt%20output%20if%20workers%20rev%20their%20engines%20for%20too%20long%2C%20workplace%20observers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20work%20more%20hours%2C%20there's%20often%20a%20diminishing%20return%2C%20said%20John%20P.%20Trougakos%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto.%20Too%20much%20time%20on%20the%20job%20can%20lead%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20errors%20and%20a%20drop%20in%20motivation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20people%20taking%20longer%20to%20do%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20work%20than%20they%20would%20do%20when%20they%20were%20fresher%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20stronger%20performance%20tends%20to%20come%20in%20shorter%2C%20focused%20bursts%2C%20Trougakos%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20understandable%2C%20he%20said%2C%20given%20the%20pressure%20leaders%20face%2C%20why%20some%20might%20want%20workers%20around%20more%2C%20though%20the%20prescription%20isn't%20necessarily%20going%20to%20yield%20better%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrin%20seems%20to%20be%20after%20better%20outcomes.%20In%20the%20memo%2C%20he%20referenced%20the%20fight%20for%20AI%20dominance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompetition%20has%20accelerated%20immensely%20and%20the%20final%20race%20to%20AGI%20is%20afoot%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Times%2C%20referring%20to%20artificial%20general%20intelligence.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20all%20the%20ingredients%20to%20win%20this%20race%2C%20but%20we%20are%20going%20to%20have%20to%20turbocharge%20our%20efforts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20requires%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b67545a4-f015-432b-997e-d7ccd676d5f8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELike%20professional%20athletes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELonger%20hours%20can%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20be%20an%20issue%20of%20%26quot%3Boptics%2C%26quot%3B%20Trougakos%20said%20%E2%80%94%20a%20display%20of%20how%20dedicated%20people%20are%20to%20an%20organization%20rather%20than%20what%20they%20get%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it's%20hard%20to%20put%20a%20number%20on%20the%20ideal%20number%20of%20hours%20for%20so-called%20knowledge%20work%20because%20it%20tends%20to%20be%20different%20from%20something%20like%20manufacturing%2C%20where%20more%20time%20spent%20assembling%20widgets%20would%20yield%20more%20widgets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20with%20desk%20jobs%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20spend%2060%20hours%20on%20the%20clock%20and%20be%20very%20unproductive%2C%26quot%3B%20Trougakos%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeidi%20Golledge%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Jobot%2C%20a%20consulting%20and%20recruiting%20firm%20that%20uses%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20likens%20her%20employees%20to%20professional%20athletes%20who%20need%20to%20rest%20between%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20time%20to%20recover%2C%20she%20told%20BI%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20can't%20play%20at%20the%20same%20level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20tech%20exec%2C%20Golledge%20said%2C%20she%20believes%20in%20%26quot%3Bburstable%20bandwidth%26quot%3B%20for%20her%20workers.%20That%20means%20if%20there's%20a%20key%20deadline%2C%20they%20can%20expect%20to%20put%20in%20more%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20work%20a%20bit%20harder%20on%20those%20days%2C%20but%20you%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20rest%20and%20recharge%2C%20and%20then%20you%20can%20come%20at%20the%20problem%20anew%2C%26quot%3B%20Golledge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2263e8a6a2-4932-4258-8c41-8fb95602f686%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20recipe%20for%20burnout%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELaura%20Vanderkam%2C%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BTranquility%20by%20Tuesday%26quot%3B%20and%20other%20books%20about%20time%20management%2C%20has%20studied%20the%20time%20logs%20of%20various%20types%20of%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20BI%20that%20few%20people%20consistently%20work%20more%20than%2060%20hours%2C%20partly%20because%20doing%20so%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-beat-employee-burnout-symptoms-work-deloitte-human-sustainability-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elead%20to%20burnout%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVanderkam%20also%20said%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20a%20round%20number%20like%2060%20would%20be%20the%20ideal%20amount%20of%20time%20to%20work.%20It's%20similar%20to%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalking-10000-steps-for-health-not-science-based-in-marketing-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E10%2C000%20steps%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20round%20number%2C%20though%20not%20one%20tied%20to%20scientific%20benchmarks%20for%20good%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20quantify%20how%20much%20time%20people%20need%20to%20be%20working%20because%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20major%20innovation%20could%20come%20at%20any%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20minute%20where%20they%20got%20that%20breakthrough%20is%20worth%2050%20hours%20of%20sitting%20around%20doing%20nothing%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20Vanderkam%20