arefoot%20in%20your%20own%20house%20is%20anti-American.%20I%20guess%20too%20many%20people%20grew%20up%20on%20sitcoms%20where%20they%20wear%20their%20shoes%20in%20bed.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FJVfJMa6VKe%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FJVfJMa6VKe%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Ian%20Miles%20Cheong%20(%40stillgray)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fstillgray%2Fstatus%2F1895485277403287798%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EFebruary%2028%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20Cheong's%20defense%2C%20many%20critics%20continued%20to%20express%20their%20outrage%20on%20social%20media.%20One%20user%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BVivek%20will%20never%20be%20governor%20of%20Ohio.%20This%20is%20unacceptable%20for%20America.%26quot%3B%20Another%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20at%20least%20have%20some%20socks%20on%20while%20you%20interview%20for%20a%20position%20in%20the%20most%20powerful%20empire%20on%20the%20planet%2C%20yeah%3F%26quot%3B%20A%20third%20user%20took%20issue%20with%20Ramaswamy's%20choice%20to%20go%20shoeless%2C%20writing%2C%20%26quot%3BVivek%20lectures%20us%20about%20education%20while%20barefoot.%20Uncivilised.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20not%20everyone%20was%20critical%20of%20Ramaswamy's%20actions.%20Many%20users%20came%20to%20his%20defense%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20removing%20shoes%20indoors%20is%20a%20common%20practice%20in%20many%20cultures%2C%20including%20in%20South%20and%20East%20Asia.%20%E2%80%9CNearly%20all%20Indians%20go%20barefoot%20in%20their%20own%20homes.%20There's%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20it.%20Just%20a%20cultural%20thing%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20user%20commented%2C%20while%20another%20added%20another%20comment%20about%20Indian%20tradition%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20Indian%20tradition%2C%20it%20is%20customary%20to%20take%20off%20your%20shoes%20before%20entering%20someone's%20home%2C%20considered%20a%20sign%20of%20respect%20and%20hygiene%2C%20as%20it%20prevents%20bringing%20dirt%20and%20germs%20from%20ou